\par \pard\plain \ri289\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright \f17\lang3081\cgrid {\f0 
\par Under the }{\i\f0 Broadcasting Services Act 1992}{\f0  (the Act) there 
are two main heads of power available to the ABA for gathering information. They are the power under s170 to conduct an investigation and the power under s182 to conduct a hearing. Both powers are available to the ABA for the purpose of exercising any of 
i
ts functions and powers under the Act. The ABA decided to undertake an investigation based on the general investigations power pursuant to s170 of the Act. The s170 power provides for an investigation to be carried out quickly and economically as required
 by s168(2) of the Act.
\par Section 158 relevantly provides:
\par }\pard \li720\ri289\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright {\f0 158. The primary functions of the ABA are:
\par ...
\par (l) to monitor and investigate complaints concerning broadcasting services (including national broadcasting services); and
\par ...
\par (n) to monitor, and to report to the Minister on, the operation of this Act.
\par 
\par }\pard \ri289\sa120\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright {\f0 Section 170 provides:
\par }\pard \li720\ri289\sa120\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright {\f0 s170. The ABA may conduct investigations for the purposes of the performance or exercise of any of its functions and powers.}{\b\f0 
\par }\pard \ri289\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright {\f0 
\par Section 168 provides: 
\par }\pard \li720\ri289\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright {\f0 168.(1) In informing itself on any matter relevant to its functions, the ABA:
\par (a) may consult with such persons, bodies and groups as it thinks fit, and may form consultative committees for that purpose; and
\par (b) may conduct investigations and hold hearings; and
\par (c) may otherwise inform itself in any manner it thinks fit.
\par 
\par (2) Subject to any directions by the Minister under this Part, the procedure that the ABA adopts in informing itself on any matter relevant to its functions is to be that which the ABA considers:
\par (a) will be the quickest and most economical in the circumstances; and
\par (b) will also promote the due administration of this Act.
\par 
